705259f-b.title: Brooklyn: Kings Highway - Avenue H
705259f-b.text:
(1)
Kings Highway, north from Ave. E. At the left is the Manhattan Beach Division of the Long Island R.R. The barns etc. at right were John Ditmars. They were in existence in 1900. The dirt road now Kingshighway, was known as the Road from Flatlands to New Lots.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
The same, showing only the railroad.
May 1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(3)
The same as No. 1.
May 1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(4)
The same, looking northeast from Utica Ave.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

705256f-a.title: Brooklyn: Kings Highway - Avenue H
705256f-a.text:
Kings Highway, north from Ave. H, showing the James Ditmars House on the left and the ruins of the Garret Kouwenhoven House on the right.
May 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
